{
  "text": "For each G ∈ B bs (Γ X,0 ) and each γ ∈ Γ X , the series η⋐γ G(η) is always finite, and moreover, (KG)(·) is a B(Γ X )-measurable function on Γ X (cf. [CITATION_1] Proposition 3.5] ).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "122832312"
